---
name: docs
description: Update documentation after code changes
user-invocable: true
allowed-tools:
  - Bash(git *)
  - Read
  - Glob
  - Grep
  - Edit
  - Write
---

Update documentation to reflect recent code changes:

1. Run `git diff --name-only HEAD~1..HEAD` (or `--staged` if uncommitted) to find what changed.
2. Check if any of the following need updates:
   - `docs/plan.md` — mark completed tasks, add new ones
   - `CLAUDE.md` — new commands, changed structure, new conventions
   - `README.md` — setup instructions, feature descriptions
   - `CHANGELOG.md` — if the project maintains one
3. For each doc that needs updating, make the minimal edit to keep it accurate.
4. Do NOT rewrite docs unnecessarily — only update what's stale or missing.
5. Report what was updated and why.
